image.altText: A steelworker in Whyalla holds his GFG helmet.

props.synopsis: Whyalla has been no stranger to emotional rollercoasters in recent years, and while some locals are wary of false dawns and keen to avoid past mistakes, the mood among the steelmaking city's business operators has been buoyed by news of the joint state and federal $2.4 billion support package.

image.altText: A green sign for Hydrogen Power SA erected on a vacant arid site in Whyalla

props.synopsis: The South Australian Government's plan to build a major hydrogen electrolyser and power plant near Whyalla has been scrapped, with the Premier Peter Malinauskas blaming the lack of progress on a plan for green steel at the local steelworks for the decision.
